<paragraph id="8163A27CFF5BCE8BFF77FAF1DA1C3915" blockId="214.[136,335,1312,1339]" box="[136,335,1312,1339]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">
<heading id="DA2B1510FF5BCE8BFF77FAF1DA1C3915" bold="true" box="[136,335,1312,1339]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFF77FAF1DA1C3915" bold="true" box="[136,335,1312,1339]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">
Group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFF1DFAF1DA1C3915" authority="Perty, 1833" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[226,335,1312,1339]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFF1DFAF1DA1C3915" bold="true" box="[226,335,1312,1339]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF5BCE8BFF77FAB4DED7394F" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF5BCE8BFF77FAB4DA5F3428" blockId="214.[136,778,1381,2093]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFF77FAB4DA513951" bold="true" box="[136,258,1381,1407]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species in the group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFDDAFAB4D9D93951" box="[549,650,1381,1407]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFDDAFAB4D9D93951" box="[549,650,1381,1407]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are readily recognized by discontinuous thoracic fovea that is interrupted in middle (
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF5BCE8BFE70FA63D85539E2" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[399,774,1457,1484]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 42 A) and the sternum with a deep central depression (
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF5BCE8BFF70FA2FDAA53A36" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." box="[143,502,1533,1560]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 42 B). The resemble all other species of 
<typeStatus id="5E671CDEFF5BCE8BFEA0F9F5DADC3A10" box="[351,399,1572,1598]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">type</typeStatus>
II morphology proposed by Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018 (which include most species described here) by triangular shape of the post-labial sigilla, sternal sigilla I–II elongated, and, in females, by the abundant retrolateral thorns on tibia II and by the lobed spermathecae. They resemble 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFDC6F933D9953AD2" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[569,710,1762,1788]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFDC6F933D9953AD2" box="[569,710,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF5BCE8BFD23F933DB9C3B0C" captionStart="FIGURE 107" captionStartId="117.[136,235,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,196,1142]" captionTargetId="figure-395@117.[151,1436,189,1145]" captionTargetPageId="117" captionText="FIGURE 107. Actinopus crassipes (Keyserling, 1891), male: A–C MCN 30740: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral.PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal TegularApophysis; PAc-ProlateralAccessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597460/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 107 A</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFF1CF8D9DAE63B0C" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1923" box="[227,437,1800,1826]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubiomaculatus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFF1CF8D9DAE63B0C" box="[227,437,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. dubiomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF5BCE8BFE3AF8D9D96D3B0C" box="[453,574,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURE 112" captionStartId="124.[136,235,1048,1072]" captionTargetBox="[232,1413,206,1008]" captionTargetId="figure-347@124.[151,1436,189,1024]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURE 112 A–C. Actinopus dubiomaculatus Mello-Leit„o, 1923, male: A–C MZSP 7636: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc- Prolateral Accessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597470/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 112 A</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFD83F8D9D85A3B0C" box="[636,777,1800,1826]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFD83F8D9D85A3B0C" box="[636,777,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF5BCE8BFF6FF8FFDA453B66" box="[144,278,1838,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 129" captionStartId="142.[136,235,1421,1445]" captionTargetBox="[176,1391,200,1372]" captionTargetId="figure-233@142.[151,1435,189,1397]" captionTargetPageId="142" captionText="FIGURE 129. Actinopus laventana sp. nov., male: A–C LZI M135: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D FCE-MY 977: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597508/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 129 A</figureCitation>
), included on group 
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFDEBF8FED9D53B67" box="[532,646,1839,1865]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">crassipes¸</emphasis>
by the PA continuous to PI. Females of group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFDDAF885D9D93B40" box="[549,650,1876,1902]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFDDAF885D9D93B40" box="[549,650,1876,1902]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">goloboffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share with 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFF77F8ABDA313BBA" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1923" box="[136,354,1914,1940]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubiomaculatus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFF77F8ABDA313BBA" box="[136,354,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. dubiomaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF5BCE8BFE86F8ABDA8C3BBA" box="[377,479,1914,1940]" captionStart="FIGURE 112" captionStartId="124.[136,235,1048,1072]" captionTargetBox="[232,1413,206,1008]" captionTargetId="figure-347@124.[151,1436,189,1024]" captionTargetPageId="124" captionText="FIGURE 112 A–C. Actinopus dubiomaculatus Mello-Leit„o, 1923, male: A–C MZSP 7636: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc- Prolateral Accessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597470/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
D–H) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFD8BF8ABD85A3BBA" box="[628,777,1914,1940]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFD8BF8ABD85A3BBA" box="[628,777,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF5BCE8BFF6FF871DA5F3B95" box="[144,268,1952,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 129" captionStartId="142.[136,235,1421,1445]" captionTargetBox="[176,1391,200,1372]" captionTargetId="figure-233@142.[151,1435,189,1397]" captionTargetPageId="142" captionText="FIGURE 129. Actinopus laventana sp. nov., male: A–C LZI M135: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D FCE-MY 977: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597508/files/figure.png" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Fig. 129 D</figureCitation>
) the similar shape of receptacles. They differ from 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFF37F816DA0B3BCE" box="[200,344,1990,2017]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laventana">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFF37F816DA0B3BCE" box="[200,344,1990,2017]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">A. laventana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of lateral swelling on receptacles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF5BCE8BFF42F7C3DED7394F" blockId="214.[136,778,1381,2093]" lastBlockId="214.[810,1451,1312,1377]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFF42F7C3DADD3402" bold="true" box="[189,398,2066,2092]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF5BCE8BFE66F7C2D8553402" authority="Rios, 2014" authorityName="Rios" authorityYear="2014" box="[409,774,2066,2093]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goloboffi">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF5BCE8BFE66F7C2D92A3402" box="[409,633,2066,2093]" italics="true" pageId="214" pageNumber="215">Actinopus goloboffi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF5BCE8BFD7BF7C3D8553402" author="Rios, D. T." box="[644,774,2066,2092]" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" pagination="73 - 77" refId="ref140396" refString="Rios, D. T. (2014) A new species of the genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) from Argentina. Acta Arachnologica, 63 (2): 73 - 77. https: // doi. org / 10.2476 / asjaa. 63.73" type="journal article" year="2014">Ríos, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
